<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="102" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
When they resurrected 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hilger, HH" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="19 - 51" publicationUrl="http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/schweiz/bj/2003/00000125/00000001/art00002" refId="B23" refString="Hilger, HH, Diane, N, 2003. A systematic analysis of Heliotropiaceae (Boraginales) based on trnL and ITS1 sequence data. Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 125 (1): 19 - 51, http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/schweiz/bj/2003/00000125/00000001/art00002" title="A systematic analysis of Heliotropiaceae (Boraginales) based on trnL and ITS 1 sequence data." url="http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/schweiz/bj/2003/00000125/00000001/art00002" volume="125" year="2003">Hilger and Diane (2003</bibRefCitation>
: 42) said that &quot;summarizing all urges a formal taxonomic recombination of EUPLOCA, including all species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Orthostachys" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium subsp. section" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Orthostachys" species="foliatum" subSpecies="section">Heliotropium section Orthostachys</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Endl." authorityName="Endl." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Schleidenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schleidenia" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Schleidenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Foerther, 1998" authorityName="Foerther" authorityYear="1998" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Hilgeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hilgeria" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Streptophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Hilgeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the oldest available generic name in this group.&quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium foliatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium foliatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the type of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium subsp. sect." order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Orthostachys" species="foliatum" subSpecies="sect.">Heliotropium sect. Orthostachys</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="3 - 73" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/122400page/1/mode/1up" refId="B26" refString="Johnston, IM, 1928. Studies in the Boraginaceae VII. The South American Species of Heliotropium. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium 81: 3 - 73, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/122400page/1/mode/1up" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VII. The South American Species of Heliotropium." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/122400page/1/mode/1up" volume="81" year="1928">Johnston 1928</bibRefCitation>
: 46). Although it is recognized as a good species (example: 
<bibRefCitation author="Foerther, H" journalOrPublisher="Sendtnera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="35 - 241" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" refId="B15" refString="Foerther, H, 1998. Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae). Sendtnera 5: 35 - 241, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" title="Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" volume="5" year="1998">
<normalizedToken originalValue="FÃ¶rther">Foerther</normalizedToken>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
: 195), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium foliatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium foliatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not transferred to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until now. Robert Brown did not cite a type collection, only mentioning &quot;v. v.&quot; (=seen alive).
</paragraph>
